A security guard in Kakamega County was on
Saturday reported dead after being attacked by weapon-wielding thugs. The guard, reports say, was hacked to death
by the unknown assailants at Kakamega market in the wee hours of Saturday
morning. The thugs correspondingly assaulted other
persons, currently nursing injuries at a Kakamega hospital. Area residents have since condemned the
incident saying murders targeting security guards have been mushrooming in the
region. According to them, the area has recorded
similar cases in recent months which have culminated in the deaths and
hospitalization of a number of security guards, as well as theft of property of
unknown value.  Confirming the incident, Kakamega County boss
Valerian Obore stated that security has been beefed up in the area with
additional police officers having already been deployed to quell the surging
murder cases.